Steps for Finding a Job:
<ol>
 	<li>Find an available job</li>
 	<li>Make first contact with an employer</li>
 	<li><strong>Send a resume and cover letter</strong></li>
 	<li>Interview</li>
 	<li>Get a job offer!</li>
</ol>
&nbsp;

&nbsp;

&nbsp;

&nbsp;

&nbsp;

&nbsp;

&nbsp;
_________________________________________________________________________________
<strong>Cover Letters</strong>

What is a cover letter?
<ul>
 	<li>A summary of what is contained on your resume, with additional details</li>
 	<li>An explanation of WHY you are a great fit for the position</li>
 	<li>A letter that sells the potential employer on your qualifications and invites the employer to read your resume</li>
 	<li>Further explanation of particular items on your resume (but not <em>everything</em> from your resume!)</li>
</ul>
<strong>TIPS:</strong>
<ul>
 	<li>DO Keep it to ONE page</li>
 	<li>DO use proper grammar, punctuation and spelling</li>
 	<li>DO use proper business letter format</li>
 	<li>DO make it more specific to the job than your resume is</li>
 	<li>DO NOT repeat your resume word for word</li>
 	<li>DO NOT talk about everything on your resume</li>
</ul>
&nbsp;

&nbsp;

&nbsp;
_________________________________________________________________________________
A cover letter can be broken down into seven parts, which can be seen below:

<img class="alignleft size-full wp-image-44295" src="http://p2i.pyd.org/wp-content/uploads/2018/01/Cover-Letter-Example.png" alt="cover-letter-example" width="711" height="793" />

